<subSubSection id="C306789DFFCDFF9C6BB0FA63FE7DF99A" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCDFF9C6BB0FA63FE7DF99A" blockId="7.[151,1436,1453,1586]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">
This widespread species was described from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCDFF9C69ABFA63FD36FA6E" box="[652,744,1453,1478]" name="Somalia" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Somalia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C69D1FA63FCA7FA6E" author="Forel, A." box="[758,889,1453,1478]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" pagination="38 - 43" refId="ref7134" refString="Forel, A. (1892) Notes myrmecologiques. Annales de La Societ Entomologique de Belgique, 36, 38 - 43." type="journal article" year="1892">Forel, 1892</bibRefCitation>
) and recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCDFF9C6F7BFA63FB0AFA6E" box="[1116,1236,1453,1478]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C6FC5FA63FABBFA6E" author="Forel, A." box="[1250,1381,1453,1478]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" pagination="108 - 147" refId="ref7244" refString="Forel, A. (1913) Fourmis de Rhodesia, etc. recoltees par M. G. Arnold, le Dr. H. Brauns et K. Fikendey. Annales de La Societ Entomologique de Belgique, 57, 108 - 147." type="journal article" year="1913">Forel, 1913</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCDFF9C6BB0FA1FFF0FFA42" box="[151,209,1489,1514]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C6BC5FA1FFE46FA42" author="Bingham, C. T." box="[226,408,1489,1514]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" refId="ref6206" refString="Bingham, C. T. (1903) Fauna of British India: Hymenoptera 2. Ants and Cuckoo Wasps. London, 506 pp." type="book" year="1903">Bingham, 1903</bibRefCitation>
). Within the Arabian Peninsula it is apparently restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCDFF9C6F7EFA1FFB31FA42" box="[1113,1263,1489,1514]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C6E26FA1FFF0DF9A6" author="Collingwood, C. A." pageId="7" pageNumber="572" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood, 1985</bibRefCitation>
). It is a common species at Rawdhat Khorim, abundant from April to September and declining in numbers from October to March.
</paragraph>
